<p>A bag contains <m>$d</m> marbles, <m>$a</m> are red, <m>$b</m> are green, and <m>$c</m> are yellow. If you draw <m>3</m> marbles
without replacement then what is the probability that you get all yellows?</p>  
<p><em>Leave your answer as a
non-reduced fraction.</em></p>


<!--*********************************************
            User solution input
**********************************************-->  
<p><m>P(\text{all yellow marbles}) = </m>
  <answer>$sol</answer>
</p>

